Package edu.cnm.deepdive.rps.viewmodel

Class EcosystemViewModel

java.lang.Object
androidx.lifecycle.ViewModel
edu.cnm.deepdive.rps.viewmodel.EcosystemViewModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
DefaultLifecycleObserver, LifecycleObserver
public class EcosystemViewModel extends ViewModel implements DefaultLifecycleObserver
Provides UI controller access to LiveData containers for ecosystem components. Some of the available components may not be required for the required functionality or user experience, and almost all can be obtained by observing the return value of getEcosystem(); however, as a convenience, properties of that ecosystem can be observed directly, using other methods of this class,

  • Method Details

    • create

      public void create()
      Creates a new instance of the intransitive ecosystem simulation, using the number of breeds, terrain size, and topology specified in the corresponding property values stored in SharedPreferences.

    • run

      public void run()
      Starts (or resumes) execution of the simulation. The speed of execution and the probability of random element swaps in each iteration are derived from property values stored in SharedPreferences.

    • pause

      public void pause()
      Suspends execution of the simulation.

    • getEcosystem

      public LiveData<Ecosystem> getEcosystem()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Ecosystem> containing the current ecosystem.

    • getTerrain

      public LiveData<int[][]> getTerrain()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<int[][]> containing the ecosystem's terrain contents.

    • getSize

      public LiveData<Integer> getSize()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Integer> containing the ecosystem's size. (Note that in this implementation, the ecosystem's height and width are equal; the size is thus equal to both the height and width.)

    • getInitialBreedCount

      public LiveData<Integer> getInitialBreedCount()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Integer> containing the ecosystem's initial number of breeds (it does not reflect any breed extinctions that may have taken place in the simulation).

    • getCurrentBreedCount

      public LiveData<Integer> getCurrentBreedCount()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Integer> containing the ecosystem's current number of breeds. This value reflects all breed extinctions that may have taken place in the simulation so far.

    • getPopulations

      public LiveData<int[]> getPopulations()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<int[]> containing the ecosystem's current breed population sizes.

    • getIterationCount

      public LiveData<Long> getIterationCount()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Long> containing the ecosystem's current iteration count.

    • getAbsorbed

      public LiveData<Boolean> getAbsorbed()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Boolean> containing a flag indicating whether the ecosystem is in the absorbing state, in which all breeds but one are extinct.

    • getRunning

      public LiveData<Boolean> getRunning()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Boolean> containing a flag indicating whether the simulation is running or paused.

    • getThrowable

      public LiveData<Throwable> getThrowable()
      Returns a reference to a LiveData<Throwable> containing the exception thrown (if any) by the most recent operation.
